	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The CPU should definitely be possible, as I think there's little to no difference.
<br />
<br />The PPU on the other tentacle, would be a lot more difficult. As the NES PPU is designed to output composite video and the Playchoice board is designed for an RGB PPU. It would probably be doable with some modifications, but I can't say how feasible they are. It might even be possible to use the video/sound daughter board of an NES to do most of the work. (But removing the board is such a PITA, it might be easier to make your own.)

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


